article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Andrew Cook's 20 points helped Eastern Washington defeat North Dakota 87-81 on Wednesday night. Cook had five rebounds for the Eagles (2-7). Emmett Marquardt scored 16 points, shooting 7 for 11, including 1 for 3 from beyond the arc. Nic McClain shot 4 for 12 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 5 of 8 from the free-throw line to finish with 15 points, while adding six rebounds and five assists. The Eagles snapped a six-game slide. Treysen Eaglestaff led the Fightin' Hawks (3-5) in scoring, finishing with 24 points. Amar Kuljuhovic added 20 points and nine rebounds for North Dakota. Mier Panoam finished with 16 points and two steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
